
he Tribonacci sequence Tn is defined as follows: 

T0 = 0, T1 = 1, T2 = 1, and Tn+3 = Tn + Tn+1 + Tn+2 for n >= 0.

Given n, return the value of Tn.

 

Example 1:

Input: n = 4
Output: 4
Explanation:
T_3 = 0 + 1 + 1 = 2
T_4 = 1 + 1 + 2 = 4
Example 2:

Input: n = 25
Output: 1389537


algortihn:
Approach (Iterative DP - Space Optimized)

Instead of storing all previous values, we only need the last 3 numbers.

Algorithm
If n == 0, return 0.
If n == 1 or n == 2, return 1.
Initialize:
a = 0
b = 1
c = 1
Loop from 3 to n:
d = a + b + c
Shift the values:
a = b
b = c
c = d
Return c.

logic:
Every Tribonacci number is the sum of the previous three numbers.
Store only the last three numbers using variables a, b, and c.
Calculate the next number as d = a + b + c.
Update (shift) the variables: a = b, b = c, c = d.
Repeat until n and return c as the final Tribonacci number.

Complexity
Time Complexity: O(n) (one loop from 3 to n)
Space Complexity: O(1) (only four variables are used)


soln:
class Solution {
public:
    int tribonacci(int n) {
        if(n==0) return 0;
        if(n==1 || n==2) return 1;

        int a = 0, b = 1, c = 1;

        for (int i = 3; i <= n; i++){
            int d = a + b + c;
            a = b;
            b = c;
            c = d;
        }
        return c;
    }
};
